cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DB

This paper deals with event mining from news data sources, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel data structure and probabilistic model for event mining, which involves machine learning and statistical modeling techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with large-scale data processing and storage, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
